cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the construction of finite abstractions of interconnected discrete-time control systems, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses a notion of storage function and simulation function, which are related to the concept of Lyapunov functions in control theory and can be seen as a form of logical reasoning. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper does not explicitly mention multiagent systems, but the techniques proposed for constructing finite abstractions and simulation functions can be applied to networks of agents. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper does not focus on AI, but the techniques proposed for constructing symbolic models can be useful for AI applications such as model-based reinforcement learning. 
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems): The paper deals with the construction of finite abstractions of dynamical systems, which falls under the scope of dynamical systems theory.
